Package: lunaineq
Title: Tools for Analyzing Health Inequality Metrics
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(person("Adrián", "Vázquez-Mejía", email = "apvasquez.md@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"), comment = c(ORCID = "0009-0005-7343-3389")), person("Oscar J.", "Mújica", email = "mujicaos@paho.org", role = "aut", comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-2893-4206")), person("Antonio", "Sanhueza", email = "sanhueza@paho.org", role = "aut", comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-1857-3662")))
Description: Tools for computing and interpreting health inequality metrics, including absolute and relative gaps, regression-based measures and disproportionality-based indices. Supports both disaggregated data (numerator/denominator) and aggregated indicators with population weights. Provides automatic interpretations in Spanish, English, French and Portuguese, and is designed for epidemiological and public-health monitoring applications.
